This article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump for Memorial Day, which falls on May 25, 2020. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of defending freedom and liberty and honoring the sacrifices made by American service members. It commemorates the 75th anniversary of the Allied victories in World War II and recognizes the more than 400,000 lives lost during the war. The proclamation calls on Americans to observe Memorial Day as a day of prayer for permanent peace and designates a specific hour for people to unite in prayer. It also asks for the flag to be flown at half-staff until noon and for people to display the flag at half-staff from their homes. The proclamation concludes with President Trump's signature and the date.